{"id":27704,"date":"2024-01-28T10:30:00","date_gmt":"2024-01-28T05:00:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=27704"},"modified":"2023-03-15T12:44:14","modified_gmt":"2023-03-15T07:14:14","slug":"types-of-kitchen-island-designs","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/types-of-kitchen-island-designs\/","title":{"rendered":"A Chef\u2019s Dream: 5 Types of Kitchen Island Designs For Your Home"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Read all you wanted to know about the different types of kitchen islands and which one you should get for your home.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you keep yourself updated with the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/new-style-kitchen-trends\/\">latest kitchen trends<\/a>, you probably know that kitchen islands are a hot commodity these days. A kitchen island can be a great addition to an open floor design. There are different types of kitchen islands that you can choose from to maximise the workspace in your kitchen, add more storage space or make room for an informal seating area.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Kitchen islands allow homeowners to add some style to their space as they present an opportunity to include bold colours, diverse countertops, accent stools and show-stopping pendant lighting. However, with the various types of kitchen islands available, finding the right design for your home can be daunting. So, we have brought you five incredible modular kitchen island designs that are the most popular with our clients. The best part, they are entirely customisable.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">5 Most Popular Types Of Kitchen Islands<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Kitchen Island With Plumbing<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Affixing plumbing to your kitchen island is a sensible choice if your kitchen space is limited. Instead of cramping your hob and sink on the same countertop, leaving little to no workspace, why not add the plumbing to the island? It doubles up your surface area for meal prep and chopping and you can also use it as a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/breakfast-bar-countertop-ideas\/\">breakfast counter<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-1 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-vertically-aligned-bottom is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:100%\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table aligncenter is-style-stripes\"><table class=\"has-fixed-layout\"><thead><tr><th class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\"> <strong>Pros<\/strong><\/th><th class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">  <strong>Cons<\/strong><\/th><\/tr><\/thead><tbody><tr><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Large work surface<\/td><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Limit movement in an already small space<\/td><\/tr><tr><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">No splashing of water and leftover food particles while washing dishes<\/td><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Expensive to install<\/td><\/tr><tr><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Doubles up as an informal dining space<\/td><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Requires professional plumbing work<\/td><\/tr><tr><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Use the bottom area for storage<\/td><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\"><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/28233228\/Kitchen-Island-design-with-plumbing.jpg\" alt=\"Kitchen Island design with plumbing\" class=\"wp-image-41852\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/28233228\/Kitchen-Island-design-with-plumbing.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/28233228\/Kitchen-Island-design-with-plumbing-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/28233228\/Kitchen-Island-design-with-plumbing-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/28233228\/Kitchen-Island-design-with-plumbing-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Separate your cooking and cleaning areas<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Kitchen Island With Hob<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The variant with hob affixed is one of the most popular types of kitchen island shapes among urban homeowners. Similar to the kitchen island with a sink, this is another way to separate the work areas. It simply flips the position of the hob and the sink. By affixing the hob on the island, you get a much wider space to comfortably set up all your ingredients, cooking tools and cookbooks to whip up a Masterchef-worthy dish. Add some open shelves to display your envious spice collection.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-2 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:100%\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table aligncenter is-style-stripes\"><table class=\"has-fixed-layout\"><thead><tr><th class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\"> <strong>Pros<\/strong><\/th><th class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">  <strong>Cons<\/strong><\/th><\/tr><\/thead><tbody><tr><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Large work surface<\/td><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Must be designed beforehand<\/td><\/tr><tr><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Adds value to your home<\/td><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Expensive to install<\/td><\/tr><tr><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Ideal for open concept kitchen<\/td><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Requires professional masonry\/electrical work<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/28233220\/Kitchen-Island-with-Hob.jpg\" alt=\"Kitchen Island with Hob\" class=\"wp-image-41851\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/28233220\/Kitchen-Island-with-Hob.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/28233220\/Kitchen-Island-with-Hob-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/28233220\/Kitchen-Island-with-Hob-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/28233220\/Kitchen-Island-with-Hob-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Whip up restaurant-style meals at home<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Space saving kitchen designs that offer 20% extra space!\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/06165035\/space-saving-kitchen-designs-that-offer-20-extra-space-scaled.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Kitchen Island With An Elevated Breakfast Bar<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If it\u2019s your dream to set up an informal dining space or a breakfast bar in your kitchen like you have seen in the movies, you need this kind of island. Kitchen islands with an elevated breakfast bar are one of the most common types of kitchen islands with seating. This island combines the two tasks while yet separating them such that cooking takes place on the lower level and dining on the higher. Place some <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/kitchen-bar-stools\/\">high bar stools<\/a> and there you have it. The optimal height for the countertop should be 36 inches and the bar top should be 42 inches.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table aligncenter is-style-stripes\"><table class=\"has-fixed-layout\"><thead><tr><th class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\"> <strong>Pros<\/strong><\/th><th class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">  <strong>Cons<\/strong><\/th><\/tr><\/thead><tbody><tr><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Ergonomic<\/td><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Blocks the view of the kitchen from the other part of the home<\/td><\/tr><tr><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Highly functional<\/td><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Very pricey to install<\/td><\/tr><tr><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Ideal for open concept kitchen<\/td><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Requires professional help<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/28233214\/Kitchen-Island-with-Elevated-Breakfast-Bar.jpg\" alt=\"Kitchen Island With An Elevated Breakfast Bar\" class=\"wp-image-41850\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/28233214\/Kitchen-Island-with-Elevated-Breakfast-Bar.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/28233214\/Kitchen-Island-with-Elevated-Breakfast-Bar-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/28233214\/Kitchen-Island-with-Elevated-Breakfast-Bar-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/28233214\/Kitchen-Island-with-Elevated-Breakfast-Bar-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Double-tiered kitchen island for cooking and dining<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Kitchen Island With Pull-Out Chopping Board<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A chopping board pull-out on a kitchen island is a smart way to keep your workstation clean at all times. They are easy to pull out and push back when not in use. You can attach a bin holder on the cabinet door below the chopping board to easily slide off the waste. To guarantee durability, go for scratch-resistant materials like marble, ceramic or Corian.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table aligncenter is-style-stripes\"><table class=\"has-fixed-layout\"><thead><tr><th class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\"> <strong>Pros<\/strong><\/th><th class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">  <strong>Cons<\/strong><\/th><\/tr><\/thead><tbody><tr><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Multipurpose<\/td><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Not readily available, must be customised<\/td><\/tr><tr><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Highly functional<\/td><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Moderately pricey<\/td><\/tr><tr><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Ideal for kitchen with limited space<\/td><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Requires professional help<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/28233209\/Kitchen-Island-with-Pull-out-Chopping-Board.jpg\" alt=\"Kitchen Island With Pull-Out Chopping Board\" class=\"wp-image-41849\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/28233209\/Kitchen-Island-with-Pull-out-Chopping-Board.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/28233209\/Kitchen-Island-with-Pull-out-Chopping-Board-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/28233209\/Kitchen-Island-with-Pull-out-Chopping-Board-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/28233209\/Kitchen-Island-with-Pull-out-Chopping-Board-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Space-saving kitchen island with a chopping board<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Give your home and kitchen a modular twist\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/26112006\/give-your-home-and-kitchen-a-modular-twist-scaled.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Rolling Kitchen Island Cart<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Rolling carts are the most versatile types of kitchen islands available in the market. While other types of kitchen islands are permanent, rolling carts offer a breath of fresh air thanks to their portability. It can be easily moved away when not in use. As a result, it is a great option for rented houses and small kitchens.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-3 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:100%\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table aligncenter is-style-stripes\"><table class=\"has-fixed-layout\"><thead><tr><th class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">\n <strong>Pros<\/strong><\/th><th class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">  <strong>Cons<\/strong><\/th><\/tr><\/thead><tbody><tr><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Multipurpose<\/td><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Workspace usually small<\/td><\/tr><tr><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Highly portable<\/td><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Can be heavy to move<\/td><\/tr><tr><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Ideal for kitchen with limited space and rented homes<\/td><\/tr><tr><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Affordable<\/td><\/tr><tr><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Available with many types of kitchen island countertops i.e. marble, butcher block, stainless steel, etc.<\/td><\/tr><tr><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\">Can be DIYed based on need<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/28233204\/Rolling-Kitchen-Island-Cart.jpg\" alt=\"Rolling Kitchen Island Cart\" class=\"wp-image-41848\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/28233204\/Rolling-Kitchen-Island-Cart.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/28233204\/Rolling-Kitchen-Island-Cart-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/28233204\/Rolling-Kitchen-Island-Cart-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/28233204\/Rolling-Kitchen-Island-Cart-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Mobile kitchen island for additional workspace<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"1783\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/28234124\/Spice-up-your-island-kitchen.jpg\" alt=\"Spice up your Island kitchen\" class=\"wp-image-41854\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/28234124\/Spice-up-your-island-kitchen.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/28234124\/Spice-up-your-island-kitchen-158x300.jpg 158w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/28234124\/Spice-up-your-island-kitchen-540x1024.jpg 540w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/28234124\/Spice-up-your-island-kitchen-768x1457.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/28234124\/Spice-up-your-island-kitchen-810x1536.jpg 810w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/28234124\/Spice-up-your-island-kitchen-150x285.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Some Frequently Asked Questions About Kitchen Islands<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Are kitchen islands a new trend?<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The idea of kitchen islands started in European households back in the 1800s. At the time, the kitchen had a workbench in front of the hearth or stove. The modern kitchen island was first designed by Frank Lloyd Wright in 1938 for a Minneapolis couple who frequently entertained guests.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How much space is required to install a kitchen island?<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Kitchen islands do not have a standard size. There is no one-size-fits-all feature. However, a kitchen island should not occupy more than 10% of the total area in your kitchen. This corresponds to a maximum width x length of 3.5 feet x 4 feet. A bigger island would eat up floor space and make it difficult to walk freely.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What kind of kitchen is best suited for a kitchen island?<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Ideally, kitchen islands are most useful in <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/modern-l-shaped-kitchen\/\">L-shaped<\/a> and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/straight-kitchen-design\/\">straight kitchens<\/a>. A kitchen island can serve as a breakfast counter or dining area in a straight kitchen with open walls. Similarly, if your kitchen is L-shaped and large enough to include an island, you will have significantly more storage space to keep things organised.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>We enjoyed putting together this collection of different types of kitchen islands. Each one combines clever planning, excellent aesthetics, ideal practicality and comfort for hosts, and a welcoming warmth for visitors. If you want a design that combines elements from here and there, our design team would love to hear more. So, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/contact-us\/\">book a free consultation<\/a> today!<\/p>\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row blog-form\">\n\t<div class=\"offset-lg-3 col-lg-6 bg-light\">\n<fieldset class=\"field-set\">\n<!-- <legend align=\"left\"> -->\n                    \n    <h3 class=\"widget-title text-dark text-center mb-0\">Looking For Modular Kitchens At Best Prices<\/h3>\n  \n \n     <p class=\"text-center text-dark mt-0\"> Speak to our kitchen experts today!<\/p>\n    <!-- <\/legend> -->\n<form id=\"blogContactUsFormMain\" action=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/get_quote_action.php\" method=\"post\"\n    novalidate=\"novalidate\">\n    <div class=\"form-group\">\n        <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\"  name=\"your-name\" placeholder=\"Enter your name*\" \/>\n        <!-- <span class=\"sales-txt-label\" id=\"labeltxt\">Enter your name*<\/span>  -->\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"form-row dc-falg-row\">\n        <!-- <div class=\"form-group col-md-3 guideForm\">\n            <select name=\"your-phone-ext\" id=\"id_select2_example\" class=\"id_select2_example drop-downfield form-dropdown\"\n                onfocus='this.size=5;' onblur='this.size=1;' onchange='this.size=1; this.blur();'\n                data-width=\"100%\" data-minimum-results-for-sea